article.description: Kahlil Felder scored 34 points with six assists and Oakland beat Toledo 76-64 on Saturday.
article.headline: Oakland beats Toledo 76-64
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio -- Kahlil Felder scored 34 points with six assists and Oakland beat Toledo 76-64 on Saturday. Felder was 9 of 20 from the field with three 3-pointers and 13 of 13 from the free-throw line. Percy Gibson had 13 points for Oakland (6-3), while Jalen Hayes had 11 points and 11 rebounds. Nathan Boothe paced Toledo (6-4) with 18 points and 10 rebounds. Jonathan Williams scored 14 points and Nate Navigato added 11. Felder had 17 points in the first half to lead Oakland to a 38-33 advantage at the break. A 6-0 spurt allowed Toledo to trim the deficit to three early in the second. But Nick Daniels' 3-pointer with 8:18 left put the lead back to 10 and the Rockets never got closer than six down the stretch -- Felder made six straight free throws and a layup in the last 1:07 to ice it.
